definitions.definition: To cut ( poultry ) along the spine and spread the halves apart for more even cooking .
examples: For the party, he spatchcocked and grilled some chickens.

definitions.definition: Often followed by in or into : to interpolate or insert (something into another thing) awkwardly; to sandwich (something within another thing).

main_definition: ( cooking ) To cut ( poultry ) along the spine and spread the halves apart for more even cooking .
secondary_definitions: ( figuratively ) Often followed by in or into : to interpolate or insert (something into another thing) awkwardly; to sandwich (something within another thing).
